Perform research activities to identify emerging technologies (Generative AI) and trends that may affect the Data Science/ ML life-cycle management in enterprise application portfolio.

1. Hands-on programming and architecture capabilities in Python.
2. Demonstrated technical expertise around architecting solutions around AI, ML, deep learning and Generative AI related technologies.

9. Familiarity with the transformer architecture and its applications in natural language processing (NLP), such as machine translation, text summarization, and question-answering systems.
10. Expertise in designing and implementing CNNs for computer vision tasks, such as image classification, object detection, and semantic segmentation.
11. Hands on experience in RDBMS, NoSQL, big data stores like: Elastic, Cassandra.
12. Experience with open source software
13. Experience using the cognitive APIs machine learning studios on cloud.
14. Hands-on knowledge of image processing with deep learning ( CNN,RNN,LSTM,GAN)
15. Familiarity with GPU computing and tools like CUDA and cu DNN to accelerate deep learning computations and reduce training times.
16. Understanding of complete AI/ML project life cycle

18. Good understanding of containerization and experience working with Docker, AKS.

title: APP Integration Engineer (Zapier and More)
tagsAndSkills: Cold calling,Backend,Web technologies,data science,Artificial Intelligence,SAAS,Service industry,Mentor
jobDescription:
• Your ultimate goal will be to shape and build integration APP store and connections to thousands of APPs.
  • You have experience with Web APIs. In this role, youll be working with many different APIs. You'll need to be able to dig into their documentation, build proof-of-concepts, and then build complex integrations with those APIs. Basically, youll need to know and love Web APIs.
  • You are a skilled programmer. You don't expect to come up with designs and leave implementation to others. Instead, you dig in and get stuff done. Our main tech stack is Nodejs, Angular, AWS, MongoDB and more, you ll be working with all.
  • You solve problems. Engineers write lots of code, but that is not all they do. You can recognize when something isn t working and do the work to figure out how to fix it. This could be with code, or by working with your teammates.
  • You are a skilled written communicator. eatOS is a 100% remote team and being able to communicate well is critical. Chat and video are our primary means of communication. You can communicate unfamiliar technical topics clearly and in an approachable way.
  • You want to do whats best for users. Integrations are at the core of eatOSs value to our customers, and we want to keep building ones that are of the highest quality and solve our customers needs.
  • Your experience lifts others up. You love assisting others and use your prior experiences to mentor, no matter how many or how few you have.
  • You understand that perfect is the enemy of the good. One of our core values is defaulting to action. You can ship code and systems that just work and work simply, while iterating as needed to get towards better solutions.
  • Build and maintain Integrations on the Zapier or other platforms for crucial APIs
  • Migrate applications to new APIs as the need arises
  • Dig into bugs and feature requests
  • Work with our partnerships team to solve problems for external groups
  • Help other engineers on the team and across eatOS
  • Be a shepherd for our platform and partners
  • Be available for emergencies if there is a problem with one of our apps when on-call.
  • As a part of eatOSs all hands philosophy, help customers via support to ensure they have the best experience possible.
  • You have 2 years of experience with development

A PLUS IF YOU HAVE

  • Experience in the SaaS, restaurant, hospitality, and food service industry.
  • Knowledge of restaurant operations is a plus.
  • Start-up experience (we love entrepreneurs!).
  • Experience in working virtually and with a virtual team.
  • Full/Part-time, remote, or work from office depending on location.
  • Experience cold-calling and prospecting in-person leads.
